    "body": "### Problem\n\n`nvim -u NONE -d <(xxd one) <(xxd two)` work fine \n\n<img width=\"2111\" height=\"589\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/74d79f9f-3b1b-40eb-a9ce-3f9454efe30d\" />\n\nbut  ` nvim -u NONE -c \"packadd nvim.difftool\" -d <(xxd one) <(xxd two) `\n\nseem only one file loaded\n\n<img width=\"2214\" height=\"820\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a3e6e787-3aa4-45f0-b48d-c3bc92ad35a6\" />\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n``` \ncat /dev/random | head -c 10240 > one \ncp one two\ncat /dev/random | head -c 10240 >> two\nnvim -u NONE -d <(xxd one) <(xxd two)\n```\n[payload.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/28753906/payload.zip)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\njust like without `-c \"packadd nvim.difftool\"`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2 \n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnvim only\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n~~Ubuntu 24.04 WSL~~\nUbuntu 22.04 WSL\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows terminal/tmux\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nofficial appimages release",
