            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think the core problem here is that this **process substitution <(...)** is a pipe and not a seekable file. \nCouldn't reproduce this bug on different native linux systems. I also ran a strace on my machine to find out if there is anything noticeable - nothing.\n\n\n@PEMessage \n1. can you reproduce this bug with the latest master of neovim on wsl?\n2. can you reproduce this bug with the latest master of neovim on a non wsl system?\n3. what is the output of this below on your wsl system:\n```bash\ncat /proc/sys/fs/pipe*\nulimit -a\n```\n",
