            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> can you reproduce this bug with the latest master of neovim on wsl?\n\nYes. Using latest nightly release still same \n```\nwget https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/download/nightly/nvim-linux-x86_64.appimage  #cc056d78fb2dc294bfc3daeba9db1fa3c4f6bff6\nchmod a+x nvim-linux-x86_64.appimage\n```\n> can you reproduce this bug with the latest master of neovim on a non wsl system?\n\nPartial Yes. Using Ubuntu 18.04 LTS Server + **neovim unsupport release** 0.12.3 (since official release need higher glibc) can reproduce it\n\n> what is the output of this below on your wsl system:\n\nFor wsl:\n```\n\n> ls /proc/sys/fs/pipe*\n\n/proc/sys/fs/pipe-max-size  /proc/sys/fs/pipe-user-pages-hard  /proc/sys/fs/pipe-user-pages-soft\n\n> cat /proc/sys/fs/pipe*\n1048576\n0\n16384\n\n> ulimit -a\n-t: cpu time (seconds)              unlimited\n-f: file size (blocks)              unlimited\n-d: data seg size (kbytes)          unlimited\n-s: stack size (kbytes)             8192\n-c: core file size (blocks)         0\n-m: resident set size (kbytes)      unlimited\n-u: processes                       192657\n-n: file descriptors                10240\n-l: locked-in-memory size (kbytes)  65536\n-v: address space (kbytes)          unlimited\n-x: file locks                      unlimited\n-i: pending signals                 192657\n-q: bytes in POSIX msg queues       819200\n-e: max nice                        0\n-r: max rt priority                 0\n-N 15:                              unlimited\n```\n\nFor Ubuntu 18.04 LTS Server\n```\n$ ls  /proc/sys/fs/pipe*\n/proc/sys/fs/pipe-max-size  /proc/sys/fs/pipe-user-pages-hard  /proc/sys/fs/pipe-user-pages-soft\n\n$cat /proc/sys/fs/pipe*\n1048576\n0\n16384\n\n$ ulimit -a\ncore file size          (blocks, -c) 0\ndata seg size           (kbytes, -d) unlimited\nscheduling priority             (-e) 0\nfile size               (blocks, -f) unlimited\npending signals                 (-i) 770818\nmax locked memory       (kbytes, -l) 65536\nmax memory size         (kbytes, -m) unlimited\nopen files                      (-n) 1024\npipe size            (512 bytes, -p) 8\nPOSIX message queues     (bytes, -q) 819200\nreal-time priority              (-r) 0\nstack size              (kbytes, -s) 8192\ncpu time               (seconds, -t) unlimited\nmax user processes              (-u) 770818\nvirtual memory          (kbytes, -v) unlimited\nfile locks                      (-x) unlimited\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-06-11T02:50:04Z",
