            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Interesting, your wsl ubuntu has no ulimit entry for pipe size. What does `ulimit -p` say?\n\n> Partial Yes\n\nThis is to vague. Ubuntu 18.04 LTS Server is to old for beeing a valid test case. To verify a native system, the system should be up to date.\n\nThe obvious question is, you are using WSL2 not WSL1? WSL2 runs a real linux kernel.\nCan you reproduce this with WSL2 and an up to date version of debian (prefered), fedora or arch?\nUbuntu is difficult to debug when they do their own journey with rewriting everything in rust.\n\nDoes the bug appear, if you are using another terminal (like alacritty) and no terminal multiplexer like tmux etc involved, and also without a SSH connection? \n\n(tmux or gnu-screen made no difference on my systems - everything is ok) \n\n\n",
